# Security

## Secrets
- NEVER hardcode secrets, API keys, or tokens
- NEVER commit .env files
- Load from env vars with startup validation
- Leaked secret = rotate immediately

## Input
- ALL user input validated server-side
- Parameterized queries only — no string concatenation
- Sanitize strings, enforce length limits
- File uploads: validate MIME type and size

## Data
- Passwords: bcrypt/argon2, NEVER plaintext
- Sensitive data never in logs or error responses
- Rate limit auth and sensitive endpoints
- Audit dependencies regularly
